engasse\n*Lausanne: Rue de Bourg, Place St. Francois, Rue St. Francois, Rue du Pont, Place de la Palud, Rue Saint Laurent, Rue Haldimand, Flon\n*Winterthur: Untertor, Marktgasse\n*[[Lugano]]: Via Nassa, Via Pessina\n*St. Gallen: Multergasse, Marktgasse, Neugasse, Spisergasse, Marktplatz\n*[[Lucerne]]: Old City (Hertensteinstrasse, Weggisgasse, Kappelgasse), Schwanenplatz, Grendelstrasse\n*St. Moritz: Via Serlas, Via Maistra\n*Gstaad: Promenade\n*Zermatt: Bahnhofstrasse\n\n===Turkey===\n[[File:20131208 Istanbul 041 (2).jpg|alt=|thumb|240x240px|[[\u0130stiklal Avenue]] in the [[Beyo\u011flu]] district of [[Istanbul]]]]\n\n* [[Ankara]]: [[Tunali Hilmi Street]], [[7th Street (Ankara, Turkey)|7th Street]], [[Atat\u00fcrk Boulevard]], [[Gazi Mustafa Kemal Boulevard, Ankara]], [[Mithatpa\u015fa Avenue|Mithatpasa Avenue]],\n* [[Istanbul]]: [[Abdi \u0130pek\u00e7i Avenue]], [[Ba\u011fdat Avenue]], [[\u0130stiklal Avenue]]\n* [[\u0130zmir]]: Plevne Street, K\u0131br\u0131s \u015eehitleri Street, Kemeralt\u0131\n* [[Bursa]]: [[\u00c7ekirge]] Street, Fatih Sultan Mehmet Boulevard, Cumhuriyet Avenue\n* [[Antalya]]: I\u015f\u0131klar Avenue, Konyaalt\u0131 Avenue\n* [[Adana]]: Ziyapa\u015fa Boulevard\n* [[\u0130zmit|Kocaeli]]: Fethiye Avenue\n* [[Diyarbak\u0131r]]: Ofis Street\n* [[Sakarya Province|Sakarya]]: [[\u00c7ark Avenue]]\n* [[Bolu]]: \u0130zzet Baysal Avenue\n* [[Trabzon]]: Uzun Street, Kahramanmara\u015f Avenue \n* [[Samsun]]: \u00c7iftlik Street\n* [[Van, Turkey|Van]]: \u0130skele Avenue\n* [[Yalova]]: Yal\u0131 Avenue, Gazi Pa\u015fa Avenue\n\n===Ukraine===\n* [[Kiev]]: [[Khreschatyk]]\n* [[Lviv]]: [[Freedom Prospect]]\n\n===United Kingdom===\n\n====England====\n{{expand section|date=September 2012}}\n[[File:Oxfordstreet and centrepoint.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Oxford Street]], [[London]]]]\n[[File:Shambles York.jpg|thumb|upright|[[The Shambles]] in [[York]], England]]\n\n*[[Bath, Somerset|Bath]]: [[Milsom Street, Bath|Milsom Street]], New Bond Street, Old Bond Street, Burton Street, Union Street, [[Stall Street, Bath|Stall Street]], Southgate Street, [[SouthGate, Bath|SouthGate]]\n*[[Birkenhead]]: Grange Road, Borough Road, Woodchurch Road\n*[[Birmingham]]: [[Corporation Street, Birmingham|Corporation Street]], [[New Street, Birmingham|New Street]], [[Bullring, Birmingham|Bullring]], [[The Mailbox]]\n*[[Brighton]]: [[The Lanes (Brighton)|The Lanes]], [[North Laine]]\n*[[Bristol]]: Queen's Promenade (Triangle), [[Whiteladies Road]], [[Broadmead]]\n*[[Canterbury]]: High Street\n*[[Coventry]]: Smithford Way, The Precinct, Market Way, Hertford Street, Broadgate, Cross Cheaping, West Orchards, Cathedral Lanes\n*[[Durham, England|Durham]]: [[Elvet Bridge]], Saddler Street, Market Place, High Street (Prince Bishops Shopping Centre), Silver Street, [[The Gates Shopping Centre]]\n*[[Kingston upon Hull]]: Prospect Street, [[St Stephen's Hull|St Stephen's]] shopping centre, the Prospect Centre, Paragon Street, Carr Lane, [[Princes Quay]], Whitefriargate\n*[[Leeds]]: [[Victoria Quarter|Victoria]], [[Briggate]], [[King Edward Street, Leeds|King Edward Street]], [[The Headrow, Leeds|The Headrow]], [[Trinity Leeds|Trinity]], [[White Rose Shopping Centre|White Rose]], [[Leeds Dock]]\n*[[Leicester]]: Belvoir Street, Gallowtree Gate, High Street, Humberstone Gate, Silver Street\n*[[London]]: [[West End of London|West End shopping district]] (including [[Bond Street]],<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnbc.com/id/21917314/?photo=6 |title=The World's Most Expensive Shopping Districts |publisher=CNBC |date=2007-11-21 |accessdate=2012-08-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015172543/http://www.cnbc.com/id/21917314/?photo=6 |archivedate=15 October 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> [[Oxford Street]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnbc.com/id/21917314/?photo=3 |title=The World's Most Expensive Shopping Districts |publisher=CNBC |date=2007-11-21 |accessdate=2012-08-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015172551/http://www.cnbc.com/id/21917314/?photo=3 |archivedate=15 October 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> [[Savile Row]], [[Jermyn Street]], [[Piccadilly]] and [[Regent Street]]), [[Knightsbridge]] area (including [[Sloane Street]]), [[Kings Road]], [[Covent Garden]] area (including [[Neal Street]], [[Long Acre (street)|Long Acre]] and [[Seven Dials, London|Seven Dials]]), [[Notting Hill]] (including [[Westbourne Grove]]), [[Royal Exchange, London|Royal Exchange]]\n*[[Liverpool]]: [[Bold Street, Liverpool|Bold Street]], [[Church Street, Liverpool|Church Street]], [[Lord Street, Liverpool|Lord Street]], [[Williamson Square]], [[Liverpool One]] Area (including [[Paradise Street, Liverpool|Paradise Street]], Peter's Lane and [[South John Street]]), [[Whitehall, Liverpool|Whitehall]], Castle Street\n*[[Manchester city centre|Manchester]]: [[Market Street (Manchester)|Market Street]], [[Oldham Street]], [[King Street, Manchester|King Street]], [[Deansgate]], [[Exchange Square (Manchester)|Exchange Square]], [[New Cathedral Street]]\n*[[Newcastle upon Tyne]]: [[Northumberland Street]],<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\"/> [[Grainger Town]]\n*[[Nottingham]]: [[Bridlesmith Gate]]\n*[[Oxford]]: [[Cornmarket Street]], [[Clarendon Shopping Centre]], [[Golden Cross, Oxford|Golden Cross]], [[High Street, Oxford|High Street]], [[Queen Street, Oxford|Queen Street]], [[Westgate Shopping Centre, Oxford|Westgate Shopping Centre]], [[Broad Street, Oxford|Broad Street]]\n*[[Portsmouth]]: [[Gunwharf Quays]], Commercial Road\n*[[Sheffield]]: [[Devonshire Quarter]], [[Fargate]], [[The Moor Quarter|The Moor]], [[Meadowhall Centre]]\n*[[Southampton]]: [[Westquay|WestQuay Shopping Centre]], [[Above Bar|Above Bar Street]], Whiteley Shopping Centre\n*[[Swindon]]: The Parade, Regent Street, McArthurGlen Designer Outlet Shopping Centre\n*[[York]]: [[The Shambles]], McArthurGlen Designer Outlet Shopping Centre\n\n====Northern Ireland====\n*[[Belfast]]: [[Royal Avenue]], [[High Street, Belfast|Hi