ieff|Rieff, Philip]]. ''Freud: The Mind of the Moralist''. Garden City, New York: Anchor Books, 1961\n* [[Paul Roazen|Roazen, Paul]]. ''Freud and His Followers''. New York: Knopf, 1975, hardcover; trade paperback, Da Capo Press (22 March 1992), 600 pages, {{ISBN|978-0-306-80472-4}}\n* Roazen, Paul. ''Freud: Political and Social Thought''. London: Hogarth Press, 1969.\n* Roth, Michael, ed. ''Freud: Conflict and Culture''. New York: Vintage, 1998.\n* Schur, Max. ''Freud: Living and Dying''. New York: International Universities Press, 1972.\n* [[David Stannard|Stannard, David E]]. ''Shrinking History: On Freud and the Failure of Psychohistory''. Oxford: Oxford University Press, 1982.\n* [[Richard Webster (British author)|Webster, Richard]]. ''Why Freud Was Wrong: Sin, Science and Psychoanalysis''. Oxford: The Orwell Press, 2005.\n* [[Richard Wollheim|Wollheim, Richard]]. ''Freud''. Fontana, 1971.\n* Wollheim, Richard, and James Hopkins, eds. ''Philosophical essays on Freud''. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 1982.\n{{div col end}}\n\n==External links==\n{{external links|date=August 2019}}\n{{sisterlinks|d=Q9215|c=Category:Sigmund Freud|s=Author:Sigismund Schlomo Freud|n=no|voy=no|wikt=Freudian|species=no|m=no|mw=no}}\n{{Bibliowiki}}\n* {{Gutenberg author |id=Freud,+Sigmund | name=Sigmund Freud}}\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=Sigmund Schlomo Freud}}\n* {{Librivox author |id=312}}\n* [http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/219848/Sigmund-Freud Sigmund Freud] at the ''[[Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica]]''\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.shapell.org/manuscript.aspx?sigmund-freud-treason-hitler-ww2-1936 |title=Sigmund Freud Assists Friend Paul Federn, 1936: Original Letter|publisher=Shapell Manuscript Foundation}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://essays.quotidiana.org/freud |title=Essays by Freud|publisher=Quotidiana.org}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.freudarchives.org/ |title=Freud Archives|publisher=Library of Congress}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.freud.org.uk/ |title=